Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.25,0:00:09.29,Main,,0,0,0,,As a present for our\Nclassmate Futa's birthday,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.29,0:00:13.16,Main,,0,0,0,,I went to Waka's house\Nto bake a ball-shaped cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.16,0:00:15.89,Main,,0,0,0,,But in Waka's brother Shun's room,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.89,0:00:19.10,Main,,0,0,0,,I found this raggedy old science book.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.10,0:00:25.37,Main,,0,0,0,,I had seen it in my dad's lab before\Nhe went missing three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.37,0:00:28.01,Main,,0,0,0,,But then suddenly, the book...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.83,0:02:03.77,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Year 1600\N(What is now) London, England"\N\N"Episode 2 Sorrowful Gilbert"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.10,0:02:06.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Is this the harbor?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.74,0:02:10.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is where I met the\NEastern man I mentioned before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.94,0:02:13.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Then maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.05,0:02:18.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.68,0:02:22.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.35,0:02:25.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa! If you're here, answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.82,0:02:28.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Please! Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.33,0:02:30.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Answer me! Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.43,0:02:34.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey there! You okay, little lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.03,0:02:35.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Tha--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.44,0:02:41.27,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry! Forgive me! I'm sorry! Forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.27,0:02:42.81,Main,,0,0,0,,James.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.18,0:02:46.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Dr. Gilbert!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.14,0:02:47.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.81,0:02:50.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Sorry to cut to the chase,\Nbut do you have what I asked for?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.82,0:02:54.25,Main,,0,0,0,,I did just as you asked. It's on the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.72,0:02:58.96,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't say I understand why,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.96,0:03:02.16,Main,,0,0,0,,but the further north we went,\Nthe sharper the angle became.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.16,0:03:05.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh? That's very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.73,0:03:10.44,Main,,0,0,0,,I wrote the details here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.44,0:03:12.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.37,0:03:15.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I'm very grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.01,0:03:20.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.42,0:03:25.95,Main,,0,0,0,,And thank you, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.95,0:03:27.42,Main,,0,0,0,,No need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.42,0:03:31.56,Main,,0,0,0,,That reminds me.\NDoc, you mentioned earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.56,0:03:34.63,Main,,0,0,0,,That Roman fellow...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.63,0:03:37.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, Bru...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.36,0:03:38.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Giordano?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.63,0:03:42.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's it! Giordano Bruno, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.40,0:03:43.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.54,0:03:48.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Last month, the Church\Nin Rome put him on trial
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.21,0:03:50.74,Main,,0,0,0,,to get him to take back his opinions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.74,0:03:52.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Giordano, on trial?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.34,0:03:56.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But he's been\Nlocked up for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.88,0:04:02.29,Main,,0,0,0,,If taking back his opinion would set\Nhim free, why doesn't he just do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.29,0:04:08.06,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sure his pride\Nas a scientist is at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.06,0:04:11.10,Main,,0,0,0,,It's not as easy as you make it sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.60,0:04:17.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Um... that thing you were talking about...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.54,0:04:22.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. "The Earth revolves around the sun."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.01,0:04:26.21,Main,,0,0,0,,There's a Roman philosopher\Nwho's very insistent on the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.21,0:04:29.71,Main,,0,0,0,,What? About something that obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.71,0:04:31.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.85,0:04:36.52,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. In your age, everyone knows that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.52,0:04:38.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.66,0:04:40.86,Main,,0,0,0,,That's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.86,0:04:45.53,Main,,0,0,0,,But in our day and age,\Nthe Church calls it heresy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.53,0:04:47.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.93,0:04:51.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Church and astronomy have\Nnothing to do with each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.54,0:04:58.78,Main,,0,0,0,,"Our land was created by God, and all\Nthe heavenly bodies revolve around it."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.78,0:05:03.58,Main,,0,0,0,,That's the Church's teaching.\NHe's saying it's a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.58,0:05:07.25,Main,,0,0,0,,If people realized that, it would be a\Nthreat to their position, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.25,0:05:11.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Even so... there's no reason to\Nthrow people in jail over the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.96,0:05:13.46,Main,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.16,0:05:18.20,Main,,0,0,0,,"And yet, it moves."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.20,0:05:24.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Scientists have known that for over\Nfifty years, since Copernicus's day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.74,0:05:25.97,Main,,0,0,0,,But we can't say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.97,0:05:30.74,Main,,0,0,0,,To those in power, inconvenient\Ntruths must be crushed by force.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.74,0:05:32.84,Main,,0,0,0,,But that's awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.18,0:05:36.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.55,0:05:38.32,Main,,0,0,0,,No good. I didn't find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.32,0:05:41.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Maybe you have to get in from outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.32,0:05:42.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.69,0:05:45.16,Main,,0,0,0,,You want to check around the outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.03,0:05:51.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Well... Why don't we set up\Na petition or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.63,0:05:53.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.13,0:05:55.17,Main,,0,0,0,,But as we're home now...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.81,0:06:03.51,Main,,0,0,0,,This is magnificent!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.58,0:06:07.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Interested?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.01,0:06:09.71,Main,,0,0,0,,What does it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.71,0:06:15.09,Main,,0,0,0,,It records the changes in the dip circle's\Nneedle based on the ship's position.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.09,0:06:16.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Dip circle?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.99,0:06:19.56,Main,,0,0,0,,You played with it on the ship, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.49,0:06:24.66,Main,,0,0,0,,It's a machine designed to record
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.66,0:06:28.70,Main,,0,0,0,,how far downward the\Ncompass needle is pointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.70,0:06:33.14,Main,,0,0,0,,A compass needle can point down?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.14,0:06:34.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.21,0:06:37.04,Main,,0,0,0,,A sailor named Robert Norman
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.04,0:06:41.18,Main,,0,0,0,,discovered that about 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.18,0:06:44.65,Main,,0,0,0,,But when I asked the sailors\Nabout the angle it took,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.65,0:06:47.25,Main,,0,0,0,,they said it changed depending on the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.25,0:06:49.25,Main,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.36,0:06:53.66,Main,,0,0,0,,I don't know. That's why I'm investigating.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.43,0:07:00.13,Main,,0,0,0,,But Norman's findings did teach us one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.13,0:07:03.97,Main,,0,0,0,,The theory that a compass needle\Npoints to the North Star...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.97,0:07:05.34,Main,,0,0,0,,That can't be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.34,0:07:07.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.74,0:07:10.98,Main,,0,0,0,,If the North Star were pulling\Nthe compass's needle,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.98,0:07:12.94,Main,,0,0,0,,the needle wouldn't tilt down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.94,0:07:15.25,Main,,0,0,0,,It would point up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.25,0:07:17.28,Main,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.28,0:07:21.32,Main,,0,0,0,,And if you went to the North Pole,\Nit would point straight up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.32,0:07:23.56,Main,,0,0,0,,And it repudiates one more theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.56,0:07:28.33,Main,,0,0,0,,The theory of a magnetic\Nmountain at the North Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.23,0:07:33.57,Main,,0,0,0,,If there were a magnetic\Nmountain at the North Pole,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.57,0:07:36.33,Main,,0,0,0,,then if the circle were in London,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.33,0:07:38.34,Main,,0,0,0,,the needle should be pointing at\Nabout a 20 degree angle downward.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.34,0:07:40.77,Main,,0,0,0,,"20 degrees"\Nthe needle should be pointing at\Nabout a 20 degree angle downward.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.77,0:07:41.61,Main,,0,0,0,,But...\N"20 degrees"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.61,0:07:42.47,Main,,0,0,0,,But?\N"20 degrees"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.47,0:07:42.77,Main,,0,0,0,,But?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.38,0:07:51.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.38,0:07:52.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.75,0:07:54.09,Main,,0,0,0,,You two!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.92,0:07:57.62,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.27,0:08:11.60,Main,,0,0,0,,My sister says she dropped\Nher ribbon in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.61,0:08:15.11,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.11,0:08:18.78,Main,,0,0,0,,But it's getting late. You should\Ngo home and look tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.51,0:08:23.62,Main,,0,0,0,,You're right. I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:24.85,Main,,0,0,0,,By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.85,0:08:28.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Do you know how long\Nthe lights have been on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.09,0:08:30.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, I turned them on myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.92,0:08:34.29,Main,,0,0,0,,I thought having a little light\Nwould make it easier to search.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.29,0:08:36.73,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you related to Mr. Hayase?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.73,0:08:40.80,Main,,0,0,0,,No, but my little sister is\Nin class with his daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.80,0:08:45.27,Main,,0,0,0,,And I used to help\NMr. Hayase with his research.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.27,0:08:46.77,Main,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.94,0:08:50.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Do you think I could have a look inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.78,0:08:53.08,Main,,0,0,0,,What? Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.92,0:09:00.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.46,0:09:11.53,Main,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.53,0:09:13.60,Main,,0,0,0,,A simple dip circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.60,0:09:19.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Or rather, a dip circle I made\Nbased on this phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.04,0:09:22.67,Main,,0,0,0,,I stuck this needle through\Nthe center of the float
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.67,0:09:25.71,Main,,0,0,0,,so that it balances parallel with the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.58,0:09:31.48,Main,,0,0,0,,But if I use this magnet...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.89,0:09:35.72,Main,,0,0,0,,...and do this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.13,0:09:44.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Do you understand what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.66,0:09:49.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Contact with the magnet\Nmade the iron needle magnetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.77,0:09:52.27,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.27,0:09:55.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Now the needle isn't parallel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.24,0:09:57.08,Main,,0,0,0,,It's pointing this far down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.08,0:09:59.44,Main,,0,0,0,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.44,0:10:02.08,Main,,0,0,0,,If there were a magnetic\Nmountain at the North Pole,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.08,0:10:05.25,Main,,0,0,0,,here in London, the magnetic force
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.25,0:10:09.19,Main,,0,0,0,,would probably not tilt the needle\Nfurther than 20 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.19,0:10:13.42,Main,,0,0,0,,But in fact, it's angled down\Nat about 70 degrees.  
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.42,0:10:15.53,Main,,0,0,0,,What does that tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.53,0:10:16.13,Main,,0,0,0,,The magnet is under the ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.13,0:10:18.70,Main,,0,0,0,,"S Pole"\NThe magnet is under the ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.70,0:10:20.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, effectively.\N"S Pole"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.37,0:10:21.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?\N"S Pole"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.17,0:10:21.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.53,0:10:24.80,Main,,0,0,0,,And the results of that\Ninvestigation are useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.80,0:10:25.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.87,0:10:27.87,Main,,0,0,0,,The longitudes and latitudes\Nwritten here indicate
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.87,0:10:32.21,Main,,0,0,0,,that the N pole of the dip circle's needle\Npoints further down as you go north.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.21,0:10:35.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Then, as you travel below the\Nequator, it begins pointing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.75,0:10:37.98,Main,,0,0,0,,What? It points up?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.98,0:10:39.32,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.32,0:10:42.19,Main,,0,0,0,,What is on the other side of the N pole?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.19,0:10:44.49,Main,,0,0,0,,The... S pole?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.49,0:10:45.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.49,0:10:48.63,Main,,0,0,0,,So why would the S pole point down?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.63,0:10:52.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Because there's a N pole under the ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.76,0:10:53.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.87,0:10:55.90,Main,,0,0,0,,In the north, there's an S pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.90,0:10:57.60,Main,,0,0,0,,In the south, there's a N pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.60,0:11:01.71,Main,,0,0,0,,It's like the whole Earth is a giant magnet!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.71,0:11:04.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow! I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.51,0:11:07.28,Main,,0,0,0,,But the question is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.28,0:11:10.18,Main,,0,0,0,,...how do we prove it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.18,0:11:13.85,Main,,0,0,0,,What? You don't have enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.85,0:11:16.49,Main,,0,0,0,,What we have now is just a hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.49,0:11:18.56,Main,,0,0,0,,It's not proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.56,0:11:21.79,Main,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.79,0:11:23.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Science is interesting, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.10,0:11:29.27,Main,,0,0,0,,The more you think, the more you investigate,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.27,0:11:31.20,Main,,0,0,0,,the closer you come to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.20,0:11:33.71,Main,,0,0,0,,The technology that brought you to this era,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.71,0:11:37.14,Main,,0,0,0,,was, I'm sure, the result of\Na similarly lengthy process.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.14,0:11:38.78,Main,,0,0,0,,I believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.74,0:11:43.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Humans create what they imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.38,0:11:44.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.40,0:11:58.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.50,0:11:59.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.43,0:12:02.17,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll go shut off the breaker now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.07,0:12:05.84,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to take up all your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.84,0:12:07.24,Main,,0,0,0,,It's fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.75,0:12:16.45,Main,,0,0,0,,It'll be hard to do any\Nmore tonight, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.42,0:12:18.92,Main,,0,0,0,,\N"Hayase Research Laboratory"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.92,0:12:21.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, take care on your way home.\N\N"Hayase Research Laboratory"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.15,0:12:22.99,Main,,0,0,0,,\NOkay. Let's go, Waka.\N"Hayase Research Laboratory"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.99,0:12:24.52,Main,,0,0,0,,O-Okay...\N\N"Hayase Research Laboratory"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.52,0:12:25.96,Main,,0,0,0,,\N"Hayase Research Laboratory"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.07,0:12:40.00,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. So the doctor hasn't\Nnecessarily come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.94,0:12:43.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.31,0:12:46.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Continue investigating.\NContact me if you find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.44,0:12:48.98,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mikage, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.85,0:12:52.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.30,0:13:12.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.84,0:13:20.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother, what will we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.58,0:13:24.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we have asked\Nthat policeman about Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.68,0:13:28.02,Main,,0,0,0,,If we're going to let anyone know,\Nit should be Mari's mother first.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.02,0:13:29.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Good point.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.99,0:13:34.43,Main,,0,0,0,,I wonder if the doctor\Ndisappeared like Mari has.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.43,0:13:35.73,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.73,0:13:38.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we can't let things remain this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.80,0:13:40.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's go to Mari's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.26,0:13:41.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.07,0:13:45.20,Main,,0,0,0,,I think it's ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.20,0:13:46.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Should I open it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.84,0:13:48.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.24,0:13:52.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Is this right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.68,0:13:56.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's done!\NIt's done! What a great smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.48,0:13:59.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you sure it's all right,\Nwith that much sugar?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.15,0:14:01.92,Main,,0,0,0,,It's fine! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.92,0:14:03.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.45,0:14:05.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.76,0:14:07.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.49,0:14:11.00,Main,,0,0,0,,I smell something delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.00,0:14:12.33,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.33,0:14:15.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Look at this! She's a cake-making genius!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.67,0:14:19.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! I'm not that good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.07,0:14:21.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, these look wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.57,0:14:23.37,Main,,0,0,0,,You've been so hospitable,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.37,0:14:27.58,Main,,0,0,0,,and this is about the only\Nway I know to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.58,0:14:30.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Um... let's do our best together, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.82,0:14:32.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.85,0:14:33.75,Main,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.75,0:14:34.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.82,0:14:37.42,Main,,0,0,0,,This? It's called whipped cream.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.42,0:14:39.46,Main,,0,0,0,,No, in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.89,0:14:46.50,Main,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd try out some ball-shaped cakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.50,0:14:49.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Today's my friend's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.07,0:14:53.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, that's back in my\Nown time, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.04,0:14:57.68,Main,,0,0,0,,If you make it too big, then the batter\Ndoesn't cook all the way through.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.68,0:15:01.35,Main,,0,0,0,,So I thought if I baked thinner cakes,\Ncut them into circles and layered them,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.35,0:15:04.52,Main,,0,0,0,,then coated them with fresh cream...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.52,0:15:07.29,Main,,0,0,0,,I see. That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.29,0:15:10.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Gilbert! Mr. Gilbert!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.79,0:15:12.46,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.23,0:15:16.43,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.43,0:15:17.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.23,0:15:19.23,Main,,0,0,0,,You've inspired me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.23,0:15:20.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks to this cake,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.77,0:15:23.37,Main,,0,0,0,,I've figured out how to prove my hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.37,0:15:25.17,Main,,0,0,0,,A model! A model!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.17,0:15:26.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.47,0:15:29.24,Main,,0,0,0,,If I file down a magnet\Ninto a model of the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.24,0:15:32.91,Main,,0,0,0,,it will unlock the secret\Nof the dip circle's needle!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.08,0:15:35.98,Main,,0,0,0,,This is incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.98,0:15:37.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.65,0:15:40.72,Main,,0,0,0,,A letter from Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.72,0:15:42.05,Main,,0,0,0,,From Rome?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.83,0:15:50.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.56,0:15:54.13,Main,,0,0,0,,It can't be. Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.13,0:15:56.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Wh-What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.34,0:16:05.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Giordano Bruno... has been put to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.35,0:16:13.58,Main,,0,0,0,,It apparently happened this month,\Non the seventeenth of February.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.13,0:16:25.90,Main,,0,0,0,,"And yet, it moves."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.90,0:16:27.90,Main,,0,0,0,,There's only one truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.80,0:16:30.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Gilbert...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.70,0:16:36.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Is this still happening in your age?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.57,0:16:41.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Those who cry the truth, persecuted\Nand murdered by those in power?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.25,0:16:45.12,Main,,0,0,0,,What an inauspicious time we live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.12,0:16:48.69,Main,,0,0,0,,I never even thought about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.07,0:17:05.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.20,0:17:07.14,Main,,0,0,0,,She disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.14,0:17:08.91,Main,,0,0,0,,She went home?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.78,0:17:14.28,Main,,0,0,0,,This is... the science of the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.12,0:17:20.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.93,0:17:32.50,Main,,0,0,0,,It hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.93,0:17:35.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.67,0:17:37.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.97,0:17:44.64,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah! I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.71,0:17:49.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.85,0:17:52.42,Main,,0,0,0,,I've been so worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.35,0:17:56.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Stupid Mari...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.72,0:18:01.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka... I'm sorry I worried you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.23,0:18:05.70,Main,,0,0,0,,You really did. But I'm so glad you're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.70,0:18:06.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.83,0:18:11.87,Main,,0,0,0,,That reminds me! How long have I been gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.87,0:18:14.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother? What time is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.67,0:18:18.71,Main,,0,0,0,,About half past eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.71,0:18:21.41,Main,,0,0,0,,So about three and a half hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.41,0:18:23.81,Main,,0,0,0,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.81,0:18:26.52,Main,,0,0,0,,It was over two days over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.99,0:18:33.09,Main,,0,0,0,,I told you, I'm staying\Nat Waka's house tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.09,0:18:36.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka's mom already agreed to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.80,0:18:40.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.80,0:18:43.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, Mama wants to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.20,0:18:47.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.24,0:18:51.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, we're just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.21,0:18:55.58,Main,,0,0,0,,What? I see. The PTA meeting next week...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.09,0:19:02.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother, how did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.99,0:19:07.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, everything in the book has disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.59,0:19:12.50,Main,,0,0,0,,But it seems to be true that Mari\Ntraveled back to London in 1600.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.50,0:19:16.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.97,0:19:18.87,Main,,0,0,0,,"William Gilbert.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.87,0:19:22.31,Main,,0,0,0,,1544-1603.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.31,0:19:24.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Inventor of the dip circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.61,0:19:27.18,Main,,0,0,0,,With an experiment using\Nan Earth-shaped magnet,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.18,0:19:30.88,Main,,0,0,0,,he proved that the Earth\Nwas a giant magnetic body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.88,0:19:36.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, Gilbert became\Nthe first person in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.19,0:19:40.96,Main,,0,0,0,,to clearly differentiate a\Nmagnet's ability to attract iron
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.96,0:19:43.23,Main,,0,0,0,,from the light attraction created\Nby static electricity in amber.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.23,0:19:49.40,Main,,0,0,0,,This discovery was one of the first stepping\Nstones to humanity harnessing electricity."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.83,0:19:52.44,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.44,0:19:55.37,Main,,0,0,0,,He really did get to prove it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.37,0:20:00.71,Main,,0,0,0,,It's possible that Dr. Hayase's disappearance\Nhas something to do with this book, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.71,0:20:02.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I bet you're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.58,0:20:03.65,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.65,0:20:06.02,Main,,0,0,0,,This is a homework assignment from Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.02,0:20:09.69,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm going to keep searching\Nfor the truth, like Mr. Gilbert,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.69,0:20:12.22,Main,,0,0,0,,and find Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.56,0:20:15.06,Main,,0,0,0,,That sounds so fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.06,0:20:17.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Like a tour of famous times in history!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.19,0:20:20.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Take me with you, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.00,0:20:23.80,Main,,0,0,0,,But only after we make Futa's cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.80,0:20:25.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.10,0:20:27.37,Main,,0,0,0,,I forgot about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.37,0:20:31.04,Main,,0,0,0,,I hope they're not\Ngetting in over their heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.22,0:20:41.52,Main,,0,0,0,,So bored...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.52,0:20:42.89,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.46,0:20:46.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you should be up?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.36,0:20:48.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.39,0:20:50.86,Main,,0,0,0,,As you can see, I'm just fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.86,0:20:55.57,Main,,0,0,0,,I was just in for tests. They should\Nlet me out today if nothing comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.57,0:20:58.94,Main,,0,0,0,,But your brother seriously saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.94,0:21:03.31,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll come by to thank him myself later,\Nbut give my regards in the meantime, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.31,0:21:03.64,Main,,0,0,0,,"Vending Machine Contains AED"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.64,0:21:04.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!\N\N"Vending Machine Contains AED"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.91,0:21:09.55,Main,,0,0,0,,But we have a reward for you, too.\N\N"Vending Machine Contains AED"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.55,0:21:12.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Happy birthday to you! Happy birthday to you!\N\N"Vending Machine Contains AED"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.28,0:21:15.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Happy birthday to you! Happy birthday to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.69,0:21:20.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Happy birthday, dear Futa!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.52,0:21:24.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Happy birthday to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.10,0:21:28.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow, are you kidding me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.37,0:21:31.60,Main,,0,0,0,,It's so cool! Is this my birthday cake?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.60,0:21:35.64,Main,,0,0,0,,After everything that happened,\NI thought everyone forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.64,0:21:38.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka would never forget!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.94,0:21:44.28,Main,,0,0,0,,But how did you even make this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.28,0:21:48.19,Main,,0,0,0,,I got a lot of thinking done\Nat this old scientist's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.19,0:21:50.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Old scientist?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.39,0:21:51.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.52,0:21:56.53,Main,,0,0,0,,But I guess you're pretty glad humans\Nlearned to harness electricity, huh, Futa?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.53,0:21:59.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.20,0:22:03.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, it's because scientists work\Nso hard to invent all kinds of things
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.83,0:22:06.47,Main,,0,0,0,,that we can live the way we do now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.97,0:22:10.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Science is interesting, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.47,0:22:10.64,Main,,0,0,0,,"Happy Birthday, Futa"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.64,0:22:12.68,Main,,0,0,0,,What's with her?\N\N"Happy Birthday, Futa"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.68,0:22:14.08,Main,,0,0,0,,She's been through a lot.\N\N"Happy Birthday, Futa"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.08,0:22:15.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!\N\N"Happy Birthday, Futa"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.41,0:22:15.95,Main,,0,0,0,,"Happy Birthday, Futa"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.05,0:22:21.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Look at this! It matches up perfectly\Nwith the numbers James brought me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.29,0:22:22.79,Main,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.79,0:22:25.29,Main,,0,0,0,,The Earth really is a giant magnet!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.29,0:22:25.76,Main,,0,0,0,,The Earth really is a giant magnet!\N\N"Next Episode:\NFranklin's Spirit of Defiance"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.76,0:22:27.99,Main,,0,0,0,,This is an incredible discovery!\N\N"Next Episode:\NFranklin's Spirit of Defiance"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.99,0:22:29.96,Main,,0,0,0,,\N\N"Next Episode:\NFranklin's Spirit of Defiance"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.05,0:24:00.62,Main,,0,0,0,,\N\N"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.62,0:24:02.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!\N\N"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.82,0:24:08.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Gilbert said Earth was a giant magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.29,0:24:10.69,Main,,0,0,0,,But I have no idea what he's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.69,0:24:11.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Me neither!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.66,0:24:11.93,Main,,0,0,0,,"Crust\NMantle\NOuter Core Inner Core"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.93,0:24:15.07,Main,,0,0,0,,The Earth is made up of four layers.\N"Crust\NMantle\NOuter Core Inner Core"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.07,0:24:17.20,Main,,0,0,0,,The outer core is believed to contain\Niron, nickel, and other things,\N"Crust\NMantle\NOuter Core Inner Core"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.20,0:24:21.04,Main,,0,0,0,,liquefied at high temperatures.\N"Crust\NMantle\NOuter Core Inner Core"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.04,0:24:23.81,Main,,0,0,0,,"Crust\NMantle\NOuter Core Inner Core"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.81,0:24:24.11,Main,,0,0,0,,"Outer Core"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.11,0:24:28.78,Main,,0,0,0,,"Outer Core"\N\NWhen the liquefied iron and nickel in the\Nouter core moves, it creates an electric charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.78,0:24:34.42,Main,,0,0,0,,"Outer Core"\N\NThis electricity flows in a ring through\Nthe outer core, producing a magnetic charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.42,0:24:34.72,Main,,0,0,0,,This electricity flows in a ring through\Nthe outer core, producing a magnetic charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.72,0:24:38.92,Main,,0,0,0,,This is why the Earth is like a magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.92,0:24:44.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, I thought there was just\Na big magnet buried in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.09,0:24:46.33,Main,,0,0,0,,If you have a magnetized metal,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.33,0:24:49.27,Main,,0,0,0,,it loses its magnetic charge\Nat very high temperatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.27,0:24:50.90,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.90,0:24:52.84,Main,,0,0,0,,We should experiment and see if it's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.31,0:25:00.81,Main,,0,0,0,,It's not sticking.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.11,0:25:05.45,Main,,0,0,0,,If we magnetize this nail with a magnet...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.29,0:25:09.79,Main,,0,0,0,,...it sticks!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.15,0:25:14.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Now let's heat this nail with a gas burner.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.43,0:25:17.73,Main,,0,0,0,,They fell!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.73,0:25:21.00,Main,,0,0,0,,The heat took away the magnet's power!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.23,0:25:25.10,Main,,0,0,0,,And since the center of\Nthe Earth is really hot,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.10,0:25:29.34,Main,,0,0,0,,that proves there can't be\Na giant magnet buried there!
